OL,3,CHeadteacher jailed after attacking his
OL,4,Cdeputy due to "sexual jealousy"
OL,6,FMr Thomas said an attack by a head on
OL,7,Ftheir deputy was, "I suspect, entirely
OL,8,Fwithout precedent" and was the result
OL,9,Fof "overwhelming sexual jealousy".
OL,11,FFollowing the incident, police said Mr
OL,12,FPyke had been discharged from hospital
OL,13,Fafter suffering minor injuries.
OL,15,FAbul Hussain of the Crown Prosecution
OL,16,FService said: "Anthony Felton struck a
OL,17,Fdefenceless man repeatedly to the head
OL,18,Fwith a metal weapon, demonstrating he
OL,19,Fhad an intent to cause his victim
OL,20,Freally serious harm.
