OL,3,CHeadteacher jailed after attacking his
OL,4,Cdeputy due to "sexual jealousy"
OL,6,F"This attack, and its aftermath, has
OL,7,Fbeen an alarming ordeal not just for
OL,8,Fthose directly involved, but also for
OL,9,Fother staff at the school, as well as
OL,10,Fthe pupils and their parents and
OL,11,Fguardians.
OL,13,F"There is absolutely no excuse for
OL,14,Fwhat Anthony Felton has done, and
OL,15,Fthere was no other possible outcome
OL,16,Fthan for him to go to prison."
